Popular Instagram skit maker, Adebayo Ridwan Abidemi who is also known as Bae U or Isbae U has apologised for his past deeds of demanding sex from ladies to feature in his skits His actions came to light this weekend after screenshots of him asking for sex from ladies to feature in his skits emerged online. Some of the ladies shared screenshots of their conversations with the skit maker on a popular blog, especially the moments he asked and begged for inappropriate videos and photos. Others who went ahead to indulge the comedian also shared video evidence of Isbae U basking in the euphoria of the moment. On Monday, reacting to the allegation, Bae U explained that the incident happened a long time ago with the lady in question. He promised to turn a new leaf and look forward to creating content. In a video posted on his Instagram page, Bae U said: “I have learnt, I am learning and I will do better. “I have sinned, I was new to skit when this girl came around a long time ago and we messed around. “I’m human and so are you and I’m not blaming anyone but myself. I have been heartbroken about this. “I pray and hope I’ll go back to making funny skits for people that think I’m creative and to make everyone happy and joyous. I just want to do skits, create videos.” He also shared screenshots where a lady blackmailed him about a video and demanded money from him.